UNITED FLIES BY ELGIN WATCH TIME
8¢
UNITED'S MARK IV DC-8 JETS HOLD ON-TIME LEAD
ON THE NEW YORK TO CALIFORNIA ROUTES
Last year, Airlift Magazine began publishing on-
time performance statistics for individual segments,
which the magazine obtained from the Civil Aero-
nautics Board.
For the last six months period . . . on the trans-
continental segments between New York and Los
Angeles, and New York and San Francisco . . .
United has an on-time performance record
well
ahead of the two competing airlines.
This lead was established with DC-8 Mark IV jets
.. flown nonstop California to New York only
by United.
And ... effective this date ... United adds 6 DC-8
Mark IV jet flights on these segments.
Schedule frequency and on-time performance ...
two reasons more people choose United than any
other airline in the world.
UNITED
THE EXTRA CARE AIRLINE
